# SlicedLabs — bat configuration.
#
# The cascade law: content rides the [ansi] SSOT terminal palette; identity and
# semantic hues live on chrome (statuslines, prompts, borders), never on body text.
# `--theme="ansi"` makes bat's syntax colours the 16 terminal colours — so bat is
# ALWAYS in sync with system/tokens.toml [ansi] by construction, with no second
# palette to maintain or drift. (A token-driven truecolor .tmTheme matching the
# nvim engine scheme is the future-richer option; ansi is the SSOT-correct default.)
--theme="ansi"

# Hairline, restrained chrome — matches the desktop's medium-weight aesthetic.
# `grid` frames the pager like a card; `header-filename` titles it (the pill feel).
--style="numbers,changes,grid,header-filename"
--italic-text=always
--paging=auto
